  <bioghist id="aspace_ecc269d487f807da9621c3570462e35f">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>A. B. Brown University, 1953; M.A. Mathematics, 1955 and Ph.D. Mathematics, 1958, University of Maryland. Professor Bramble is currently a Professor Emeritus at Cornell University and Distinguished Professor of Mathematics at Texas A&amp;M University with a research interest in partial differential equations (PDE), numerical methods for PDE, and multigrid methods.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_62e9a23b3c9ca56cfd3205579a3a79f6">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>The collection contains correspondence, notes, talks, lectures, and papers by J.H.B. and others.</p>  </scopecontent>
